<!-- HERO -->
<section class="hero compact">
  <div class="hero-photo hero-photo--team" role="img" aria-label="The Kiker's U-Pull-It team outside the Pensacola yard"></div>
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="h-tags"><span class="eyebrow on-ink">Our Story</span><span class="chiplet">Since 1972</span><span class="chiplet">3rd generation</span></div>
    <h1>A Pensacola family. <em>Three generations in.</em></h1>
    <p class="lede">We're not a faceless online buyer here today and gone tomorrow. We're a Pensacola family that's been through the hard times and come back stronger — and that history is our edge. Nobody around here has it.</p>
  </div>
</section>
<div class="hazard"></div>

<!-- VALUES -->
<section class="values-band">
  <div class="wrap"><div class="values-layout">
    <div><span class="eyebrow">How We Work</span><h2>The standard at Kiker's</h2></div>
    <div class="values-grid">
      <div class="value-item">{% include '_partials/kiker-icon' with { name: 'wrench' } only %}<b>Own It</b><span>See a problem. Fix it.</span></div>
      <div class="value-item">{% include '_partials/kiker-icon' with { name: 'paperwork' } only %}<b>Do Right</b><span>Honest work. Fair deal.</span></div>
      <div class="value-item">{% include '_partials/kiker-icon' with { name: 'fast-work' } only %}<b>Outwork It</b><span>Push harder than expected.</span></div>
      <div class="value-item">{% include '_partials/kiker-icon' with { name: 'teamwork' } only %}<b>Back Each Other</b><span>We win together.</span></div>
      <div class="value-item">{% include '_partials/kiker-icon' with { name: 'hard-hat' } only %}<b>Watch Out</b><span>Everyone goes home safe.</span></div>
    </div>
  </div></div>
</section>

<!-- STORY + TIMELINE -->
<section class="sec">
  <div class="wrap"><div class="split2 top">
    <div>
      <span class="eyebrow">The Long Road</span>
      <h2 style="font-size:clamp(24px,3.2vw,34px);margin:8px 0 12px;font-style:italic">From the dirt up</h2>
      <p class="lead-p">Hunter's grandfather bought the property in 1972. The early years were hard — at one point the only shredder between Pensacola and Birmingham wouldn't buy the family's crushed cars, and a four-hour haul north didn't pencil out. A farm-commodity crash later pushed the family into bankruptcy.</p>
      <p class="lead-p" style="margin-top:14px">They came back. In 2001 the family reopened as Kiker's U-Pull-It. Hunter was 14, breaking down aluminum wheels and setting cars on heavy wheel stands in the sand and dirt under the Pensacola sun. Not many 14-year-olds were doing that. He learned every corner of the business beside his grandfather and today runs the yard as the third generation.</p>
      <p class="lead-p" style="margin-top:14px;color:var(--text);font-style:italic">"I can let this be a crutch, or it doesn't define me — and we're gonna make the best of it."</p>
    </div>
    <div class="timeline light">
      <div class="tl"><span class="yr">1972</span><span class="tx"><b>Granddad bought the property.</b> The ground Kiker's still sits on today.</span></div>
      <div class="tl"><span class="yr">'90s</span><span class="tx"><b>Hard years.</b> Shredder politics and a farm-commodity crash tested the family.</span></div>
      <div class="tl"><span class="yr">2001</span><span class="tx"><b>Reopened as Kiker's U-Pull-It.</b> Hunter, 14, breaking down aluminum wheels and setting cars in the yard.</span></div>
      <div class="tl"><span class="yr">Today</span><span class="tx"><b>3rd generation, family-led.</b> 25 years serving Pensacola — done by the book.</span></div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="about-photo-pair">
    <figure class="site-photo site-photo--portrait"><img src="assets/photos/yard-interior-flood.jpg" alt="The Kiker's parts warehouse during a flooding event" width="765" height="1020" loading="lazy"><figcaption><i data-lucide="history" aria-hidden="true"></i>The hard days are part of the story, too.</figcaption></figure>
    <figure class="site-photo site-photo--landscape"><img src="assets/photos/counter-team.jpg" alt="Three Kiker's employees standing behind the parts counter" width="1830" height="1920" loading="lazy"><figcaption><i data-lucide="users" aria-hidden="true"></i>The crew behind the counter today.</figcaption></figure>
  </div></div>
</section>

<!-- OWNER -->
<section class="sec" style="background:var(--surface-3)">
  <div class="wrap"><div class="owner">
    <figure class="site-photo site-photo--square"><img src="assets/photos/cash-handoff-detail.jpg" alt="Hunter Kiker completing a vehicle purchase with a customer" width="2048" height="1536" loading="lazy"></figure>
    <div>
      <span class="eyebrow">Meet the Owner</span>
      <h2>The guy behind every offer</h2>
      <p class="lead-p">Hunter has worked this yard since he was a teenager. He's hands-on, straight with people, and accountable for how Kiker's treats every customer — whether you're selling a car or pulling a part.</p>
      <p class="quote">"We make it simple and we do it right — fair cash, paperwork handled, the car recycled the proper way."</p>
      <div class="sig">Hunter Kiker</div>
      <div class="role">Owner · Kiker's U-Pull-It · Licensed Florida salvage dealer</div>
    </div>
  </div></div>
</section>

<!-- MILESTONES -->
<section class="sec tight">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="sec-head"><span class="eyebrow">Milestones</span><h2>Still on the same ground</h2></div>
    <div class="plates">
      <div class="plate"><div><div class="n">1972</div><div class="l">Land Bought</div></div></div>
      <div class="plate"><div><div class="n">2001</div><div class="l">Reopened</div></div></div>
      <div class="plate"><div><div class="n" style="color:var(--amber)">3rd</div><div class="l">Generation</div></div></div>
      <div class="plate"><div><div class="n" style="color:var(--red)">25</div><div class="l">Years Serving</div></div></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- COMMUNITY / GIVING BACK (dark) -->
<section class="sec story">
  <div class="wrap"><div class="story-grid">
    <div>
      <span class="eyebrow on-ink">Giving Back</span>
      <h2>Good for the <em>community.</em></h2>
      <p class="lede">We donate vehicles to the local fire department for extrication training — practice that can save a loved one's life one day. And every car we take in gets recycled the right way: copper and metal recovered, fluids handled properly, good parts going on to keep another family on the road.</p>
      <p class="body">End of life giving life. It's not just fluff — it's how we've always done it.</p>
    </div>
    <figure class="site-photo site-photo--landscape"><img src="assets/photos/counter-team-candid.jpg" alt="Kiker's team members smiling behind the parts counter" width="1925" height="2048" loading="lazy"></figure>
  </div></div>
</section>

<div class="ecostrip"><div class="wrap"><span class="ic">♻️</span><span class="t">Every vehicle is recycled the right way — good parts reused, metals recovered, fluids handled properly.</span></div></div>

<div class="race-rule"></div>
<section class="finalcta"><div class="wrap">
  <div><h2>Pensacola's yard for 25 years.</h2><p>Sell a car, pull a part, or just come say hi. We're the people you actually know.</p></div>
  <div class="grp"><a class="btn btn--amber btn--lg" href="sell-your-vehicle.html"><span class="ic">⚡</span>Get a Cash Offer</a><a class="btn btn--outline-light btn--lg" href="contact.html">Visit the Yard</a></div>
</div></section>

